Japan Purchases 5,806 Tons of Rice From Overseas in Tender

-- B y   Y a s u m a s a   S o n g   a n d   A y a   T a k a d a
-- 
2011-03-02T09:19:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/japan-purchases-5-806-tons-of-rice-from-overseas-in-tender.html
Japan bought 5,806 metric tons of
rice in a tender today, the Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry
and Fisheries said.  Of the total, 3,936 tons were from the U.S., 1,310 tons
were from  Thailand , 440 tons were from China and 120 tons were
from Pakistan, the ministry said in a statement.  Japan is self-sufficient in rice. The nation agreed to give
minimum market access to exporting countries at the  Uruguay
Round  of world trade talks in 1993, buying 770,000 tons a year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aya Takada in Tokyo at 
